post_text:
We are definitely living in a New World! Join the Pratt High School theatre department for lots of singing and dancing as we present "Songs for a New World" written by Jason Robert Brown. Originally Produced by the WPA Theatre, New York City, 1995 (Kyle Renick, Artistic Director). Original Orchestration by Brian Besterman and Jason Robert Brown.
We are excited to provide a special performance Sept. 11 at 9:30 am for our senior citizens and vulnerable population. Bring a mask and social distance with us.
Other performances are Sept. 12 at 7:30 pm and Sept. 13 at 2:00 pm at Liberty Middle School Auditorium.
Tickets are $5. Seating is limited so reserved seating is recommended. Contact Arica Malone at arica.malone@usd382.com to reserve seats.
SONGS FOR A NEW WORLD is presented through special arrangement with Music Theatre International (MTI). All authorized performance materials are also supplied by MTI. www.mtishows.com

post_text:
Here's our latest update letter. We will send updates on Monday and Tuesday next week as well. We are excited to get school started.

Parents, we appreciate your support and ask your help on a few items to help us during the pandemic. We do have a mask for a student who needs one, but students will like having a mask they have selected for fit and style. Please help them get acclimated before school--so far, our athletes are rocking it and doing a great job. Those younger students who have visited our buildings have been fantastic. They all show the can-do, Greenback spirit which will be one reason for their success throughout their school careers and after.

Students do need a mask in order to ride the bus. I do ask that if you can bring your child to school it will help our spacing on our buses tremendously. We still offer our bus service as normal (masks required to board and while riding) but any reduction in numbers on the bus will benefit all students.

Thank you

post_text: Just a reminder that One Stop Enrollment is scheduled for Monday, August 3, 2020. If you want to make One Stop Enrollment "No Stop Enrollment" this option is available by visiting the link below- we do not have a yellow brick road - but we do have an Enrollment Road Map- if you are unable to access the necessary forms at the link below or if you are more comfortable registering on site, please come see us at the High School between 7:30 a.m. and 6:30 p.m. The majority of the registration process will take place in the High School Gym, but, we will have you enter and exit through the commons area. Any questions, please do not hesitate to contact the central office at 620-672-4500. As a reminder, masks are required while inside a public facility. Please visit the link below for your enrollment road map. https://www.usd382.com

Huge announcement from Mrs Beilman:

The National Speech and Debate Association West Kansas district awards were announced by Zoom at 2 p.m. with about one hundred coaches, administrators, and students.
Drum roll...
Both Kahrie Stegman and Colby Barradas earned outstanding awards. Kahrie EARNED THE ACADEMIC ALL-AMERICAN for leadership and academics, one of a handful in our district to win the award. And Colby Barradas will be COMPETING AT NATIONALS in DRAMATIC INTERPRETATION in mid-June, at the first virtual nationals tournament ever.

(Yes, that’s Colby after winning his nationals qualifier position via Zoom!)

Wait for it...
#smallschoolsbigopportunities

shared_text:
Theatre Kansas
April 22 at 11:37 PM ·

Today’s fourth Jester Month feature is...
🥁🥁 *drumroll please* 🥁🥁
Pratt High School ::
“Once Upon a Mattress”

Prince Dauntless and the cast sing “Opening for a Princess” 🤴🏻

Junior Colby Barradas has this to say: “The song "Opening for a Princess" really shows the inner personality of Prince Dauntless. This song follows the scene where a princess takes a test to see if she is worthy to marry Prince Dauntless -- and fails! Dauntless, seeing that everyone else at court has a ❤️ love ❤️ interest, is very sad because he doesn't. To make matters worse, since there is a law in the land stating that no other couple can get married until the Prince is married, all the people in the land are mad at Dauntless.“

A note from the School Nurse:

Today the CDC made a change in the recommendations in the use of face masks. The new recommendation is the use of cloth face coverings when you will be out in public or in situations where it may be difficult to maintain social distancing. But, please remember that everyone still needs to follow the social distancing guidelines of 6' apart EVEN if you are wearing a covering over your face. Below is a link to the continued recommended guidelines in the prevention of Covid-19.

https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/prevention.html

Stay Safe and Healthy!

post_text:
Today was the first day of the USD 382 "Grab and Go" lunches for all individuals aged 1-18, which will also include breakfast for the next morning. The USD 382 Facebook page has more details about the various pick-up sites on an earlier post.

To keep this moving forward, USD 382 Lunch Service needs to borrow 10-12 additional large coolers (preferably on wheels) for the next 8 weeks. There is not a need at this time for small coolers. If you have a cooler that can be loaned out for this period of time, please bring it by Pratt High School between the hours of 8 am - 11 am either tomorrow or Wednesday. You will need to buzz in on the west main door. To maintain social distancing, we would ask you leave it outside the main office doors. Please make sure your cooler is labeled clearly if you would like it returned. Questions - Call David Swank at 620-450-6078.

Thanks in advance for your help.

post_text:
Greenback Family,

In today's conference call, the KSDE Commissioner strongly recommended the closing of schools for this coming week. Obviously, this has little immediate impact for our community because we are already on spring break. We will cancel all athletic and activity practices for this coming week.

Again, this is all about flattening the curve (see the picture) so we can maintain very high survivability rates for our community, state, and nation. We will maintain those high survivability rates if we slow the spread and do not overwhelm our healthcare system. All of the cancellations and closures of large events (NBA games, the NCAA tournament, etc) are about taking extreme measures now in order to protect our healthcare system.

The Kansas Governor will speak at 6:00 this evening.

This situation is evolving and we will continue to make updates to our parents and students. We will announce plans for the week of March 23rd by March 20th.

I appreciate our community's calm and measured approach. We will look out for each other as we navigate these choppy seas.

USD#382 has the following classified position available. If you know of someone that has questions and might be interested, please have them contact David Inslee - - Maintenance Director

Food Truck Driver/PHS custodian - This person delivers food carts to other buildings in the district along with custodial duties in the high school. Heavy lifting is required on a daily basis when delivering food carts. Candidate must be self motivated, dependable, and work well with others and be able to take direction as given. Benefits after a probationary period include health insurance, vacation, and paid holidays. Interested applicants must apply on the district website at USD382.com. This is a full time position and previous experience is not required.

post_text: These pics are from 4 years ago when Representative Greg Lewis met with Andres Venegas as part of our job shadowing program in 8th grade. It with a heavy heart that I report that Greg Lewis passed away yesterday. He worked hard to represent his district and was a friend to education and our students, working to help set them up for success. We honor his contributions to KS. His funeral is at 2:00 on Friday at the Calvary Baptist Church, north of Stafford.
